nl: Suppose that $f$ is holomorphic in an open set $\Omega$. Prove that if $|f|$ is constant, then $f$ is constant.
lean:
∀ {f : ℂ → ℂ} (Ω : Set ℂ) (a b : Ω) (h : IsOpen Ω)
  (hf : DifferentiableOn ℂ f Ω) (hc : ∃ (c : ℝ), ∀ z ∈ Ω, abs (f z) = c), f a = f b
candidate: ∀ (f : ℂ → ℂ) {s : Set ℂ} (hs : IsOpen s) (hf : AnalyticOn ℂ f s), (∀ z ∈ s, abs (f z) = c) → (∀ z ∈ s, f z = c)
imports:
import Mathlib

open Complex Filter Function Metric Finset
open scoped BigOperators Topology
